A sorted vector is given. Find the number of occurrences of the element X, also given.

Input:
vector

Output:
number of occurrences of x

Solution:
A solution would be searching for x with a single binary search, then going left and right from that position until x is no longer found. However, in the worst-case, this could traverse the entire vector, when x is on every position.
A 2-way binary search is used, one for the first x, another for the first occurrence of x, the other for the first occurrence of an element greater than x. The result is the higher element's index - the lower element's index.

Complexity:

T: O(logn) // 2 binary searches
S: O(1) // no structures used